org.lambdacomplex.nn.javacuda
Class Context

java.lang.Object
  org.lambdacomplex.nn.javacuda.Context

public class Context
extends java.lang.Object

This class encapsulates the CUDA context. CUDA contexts are often associated with threads, so many static methods are used. Create contexts using the Device class.

Method Detail

attachCurrent

public static Context attachCurrent()
Increment the usage count on the context currently associated with this thread. When done with this context, the detach method should be called on it. Equivalent to cuCtxAttach.

Returns:
The context currently associated with this thread.

popCurrent

public static Context popCurrent()
Disassociates the current context from the thread (popping it from the context stack). The context must have a usage count of 1. The context then becomes a floating context.

Returns:
The context previously associated with this thread (the context on the top of the stack).

getCurrentDevice

public static Device getCurrentDevice()
Get the device associated with the context which is associated with the current thread. Equivalent to cuCtxGetDevice.

Returns:
The device associated with the current context.

syncWithCurrent

public static void syncWithCurrent()
Block the thread until the current context's tasks are completed. This method throws an exception if one of the tasks fails.

loadCubin

public static Module loadCubin(Cubin cubin)
Load the given Cubin onto the GPU, to ready it for use.

Parameters:
cubin - The Cubin object to be loaded.
Returns:
The resulting module on the GPU.

setFlag

public void setFlag(Context.Flags flag)
Set the flag this context uses during initialisation.

Parameters:
flag - The flag to be used.

create

public void create()
Initialise this context and associate it with the current thread. Equivalent to cuCtxCreate. Flags are set using the setFlag method.

detach

public void detach()
Decrement the current usage count by 1, if the count reaches zero then destroy this context. This context must be associated with the calling thread.

push

public void push()
Associate this context with the current thread (push it onto the stack). The context must be floating (not associated with any thread).

destroy

public void destroy()
Destroy this context. If the usage count is not 1, or this context is being used by another thread this function will fail with an exception. Equivalent to cuCtxDestroy.
